<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbf25cf4d-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s10369"><num value="10369">§ 10369.</num><heading> Research agreement authority</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary may enter into contracts, grants, or cooperative agreements, for periods not to exceed 5 years, to carry out research within the Bureau of Reclamation.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idbf28183e-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/111/11/tIX/s9509">Pub. L. 111–11, title IX, § 9509</ref>, <date date="2009-03-30">Mar. 30, 2009</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/123/1346">123 Stat. 1346</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
